Show the example of how to using YUI library in rails 3
#######################################################
Please download yui library ==> http://yuilibrary.com/download/yui3/ (in yui library folder, which you download
will has yui-min.js(/build/yui/yui-min.js)) 


1. In app/assets (add jquery and rails.js)
      |
      |_ javascripts
      |     |
      |     |_ jquery.js // version need to be > 1.6
      |     |
      |     |_ rails.js 
      |     |
      |     |_ yui-min.js
      |
      |_ stylesheets
            |
            |_ application.css (add css)


2. Create action creat_graph.haml in Graphs_controller.rb 

Remarkable: To use params in javascript for haml ==> #{escape_javascript(params[:your_params])}"

for more information about yui please visit http://yuilibrary.com/yui/docs/charts/charts-multiseries.html
#######################################################

Thank you YUI for make developper like us be able to generate the graph easier.***